Global Electric Power Assisted Steering Systems Market Insights
Electric Power Assisted Steering Systems Market size was valued at USD 26.4 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 38.7 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Electric Power Assisted Steering Systems Market Overview
The global Electric Power Assisted Steering (EPAS) Systems market is expected to grow significantly, with an estimated market value of approximately USD 26 billion in 2025. This growth is fueled by the rising demand for fuel-efficient vehicles, improved driving experiences, and a shift towards electric vehicles (EVs). The EPAS systems offer superior fuel efficiency, reduced CO2 emissions, and lighter steering, which are critical factors driving their adoption in the automotive industry. With advancements in technology and increasing consumer preference for electric vehicles, the market is poised for continued expansion over the coming years.

